&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dental Receptionist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reference No: J127-A-20-0623&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours:  22.5 hours, 3 days a week, Mon, Wed, Fri&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base: Wheatbridge, 30 Wheatbridge Road, Chesterfield, S40 2AB&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: £18,005 - £19,337 per annum pro rata&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you want to make a real difference in a socially minded, values driven organisation?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you want to work where your voice can be heard?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are an award winning employee owned social enterprise, providing high quality community dental services across east and central England.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Have you ever pictured yourself working in a dental clinic with a highly experienced and specialised team?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If your answer is ‘yes’ and you see yourself as a caring, compassionate, flexible and approachable person where you will be appreciated by patients and the team, then this is the place for you.  Your good communication skills and effortless ways of making people feel at ease will be a real asset when providing valuable support at these clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What are we looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for providing reception and administrative support in our clinics. Most importantly, we would like you to have a welcoming and upbeat approach and be a helping hand in the clinic for both employees and patients. Our clinical sessions run between Monday to Friday 8.30am – 6.00pm, and we will need you to be flexible in your approach to work. There may be a requirement to work at other clinics, so car drivers are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What do we offer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           Part time, permanent, 22.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           Starting salary gross £18,005 per year pro rata&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           Pension Scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           Learning and development opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•           Nurturing and caring work environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like any more information please contact Amanda Wilbraham, Senior Dental Nurse amanda.wilbraham@cds-cic.co.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are happy to go straight ahead with an application, please apply online at NHS Jobs quoting the above reference number.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date:           &lt;/strong&gt;19th November 2020&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Interview date&lt;/strong&gt;:        2nd Decemeber 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Head Office: Community Dental Services CIC, Colworth House, Colworth Park, &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sharnbrook, Beds, MK44 1LZ &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
